Thu May  7 13:30:53 UTC 2026 - Dominique Leuenberger <dimstar@opensuse.org>

- Do not Require/BuildRequire systemd: there is no need for it.
  During build, it's not queried and at runtime the package is
  either installed on a system managed by systemd (regular system)
  or in containers (which even when systemd would be installed, is
  not managed by systemd). The presence of service files does not
  mandate systemd being installed.

